#Text=Delhi/South East Delhi
#Text=South East
#Text=Delhi
#Text=is a district of Delhi which , like South Delhi , is high-income and with easy motorway access to the airport .

#Text=The current district borders of South East Delhi include a number of important sites near the city center , such as Humayun 's Tomb , Purana Qila , and the southeast part of planned city of New Delhi .
#Text=Get in
#Text=The violet and magenta metro lines crisscross South East Delhi .
#Text=The 405 bus service from Mori Gate Bus Terminal goes south across South East Delhi .
#Text=See
#Text=The region of South East Delhi can be further broken down into several sub regions like Naizamuddin , Humayun 's Tomb area , East Kailash , Kalkaji and Tughlakabad .
#Text=Humayun 's Tomb Complex

#Text=Humayun 's Tomb ( Urdu : ہمایوں کا مقبرہ Humayun ka Maqbara ) ( in south Delhi , near Hazrat Nizamuddin station ) . daily from sunrise to sunset . is one of Delhi 's three UNESCO World Heritage Site s. -

#Text=The tomb is in large , immaculately maintained gardens in the Persian Char Bagh ( four corners ) style that were thoroughly renovated in 2003 with the Aga Khan 's help and are consequently probably the best in Delhi .

#Text=As you pass through the first gate , you will glimpse the dome of the tomb and enter a floral path leading to the second ( West ) gate , which now acts as the entrance to the giant central garden . -
#Text=The centrepiece is the eponymous tomb of Humayun , the second Mughal emperor .
#Text=Built starting in 1562 , it was the first major Mughal structure in the city and has been described as a predecessor or prototype of Agra 's Taj Mahal .

#Text=The structures are , indeed , stylistically similar , although Humayun 's Tomb is built from red sandstone , not white marble , and was built by a wife grieving for her husband , not the other way around .

#Text=You can climb up to the second level ( the stairs on the west side are very steep , those on the south side less so ) , and on the south side you will find the entrance into the main crypt where Humayun is buried .
#Text=Before you leave , be sure to visit the South Gate , the original royal entrance , from where you can get picture-postcard views without too many tourists in the way .

#Text=The Humayun 's Tomb Complex alsohouses several other tombs and structures , including Isa Khan 's Tomb and Mosque , Barber 's Tomb , Arab Sarai , Afsarwala Mosque and Tomb and Ba Halim 's Garden and Tomb
#Text=₹ 10/250 , Indians/foreigners .
#Text=Isa Khan 's Tomb , Within Humayun 's Tomb Complex .

#Text=As you enter the Humayun 's Tomb Complex , the first major structure on your right is the bulbous , octagonal tomb of Iza Khan , a court noble who built it in his own lifetime , some 20 years before Humayun 's Tomb
#Text=Barber 's Tomb , Within Humayun 's Tomb Complex .
#Text=In the southeast corner is the Barber 's Tomb , also built in the same style .
#Text=Historians do not know who is buried in this picturesque tomb made of red and grey sandstone .
#Text=Around Humayun 's Tomb
#Text=Khan-I-Khana 's Tomb , Nizamuddin East ( 10 minutes from Jangpura metro station .
#Text=Right north of Barapulllah Elevated Rd .
#Text=This is a tomb built by Khan-I-Khana in 1598 after his wife 's death .
#Text=He was later buried here in 1627 .
#Text=Khan-I-Khana was a great composer during Akbar 's time and also belonged to his Navaratna or his nine jems .
#Text=The motif is similar to that of the Humayun 's tomb .
#Text=Kos Minar , Inside National Zoological Park . " Kos Minar , " or distance markers are pillars built by Sher Shah Suri in order to measure distance .
#Text=The distance between two Kos Minar is roughly 8 km .
#Text=They are massive pillars , 9 m high , built on a high platform .
#Text=Nila Gumbad , Located on the south - eastern corner of Humayun Tomb Complex ( Approched from outside the Humayun Tomb past the Sundar Bagh Nursery and Gurudwara Dam Dama Sahib ) .
#Text=The octagonal tomb is crowned with a huge dome , covered with dark blue tiles .
#Text=Sundarwala Mahal ( Sundar Mahal ) ( North of Humayun 's Tomb Complex .
#Text=Located inside Sundar Bagh Nursery ) . A rectangular rubble built tomb , with five arches on each side .
#Text=The chamber below houses a grave but nothing is known about its occupant
#Text=Sunderwala Burj ( Sunder Nurserym ) ( North of Humayun 's Tomb Complex .
#Text=Located inside Sundar Bagh Nursery ) .
#Text=Located within the Sundar Bagh Nursery the tomb stands on a square base and has sloped walls .
#Text=It is crowned with a dome .
#Text=It is believed to be an pre Mughal tomb but nothing is known about its occupant .
#Text=Free .
#Text=Bara Batasha ( Bara Batashewala Mahal ) , Bharat Scouts and Guides Marg , Nizamuddin ( Located in the road leading to Nizamuddin station . - North 200 m from Humayun 's Tomb ) .
#Text=This structure houses the tomb of Mirza Muzaffar who was the son of Babur and Gulrukh Begum .
#Text=The speciality of this structure is that it has 5 arches on each side .
#Text=Sabz Gumbad , Nizamuddin , Sabz Burj ? ( Located near Humayun 's Tomb . - JNL Stadium metro station about one km ) .
#Text=Now entry is prohibited inside. .
#Text=Though it literally means " green dome " , its dome is nowhere green in colour .
#Text=The dome is blue coloured and the tower is believed to be built between 1530 and 1535 .
#Text=The tower is an influence of Central Asian architecture .
#Text=There are blue and yellow tiles on the drum .
#Text=Moreover it was used as a police station during British rule .
#Text=Purana Qila
#Text=Purana Qila ( Old Fort , मथुरा रोड ) , Purana Qila , Mathura Road ( Near Delhi Zoo ) , ☏ +911124355387 . 09:00 - 17:00 .
#Text=Purana Qila is the walled citadel of Mughal Emperor Humayun .
#Text=It later turned into an urban village before becoming a monument .

#Text=Ruins of the 16th century city of Shergarh , this complex sits on top of what is believed to be the site of Indraprastha , the capital of the Pandavas in the Mahabharata epic . ₹5 for Indians , ₹100 for foreigners .
#Text=Qila-i-Kuhna Masjid , Purana Qila . 09:00 - 17:00 .
#Text=A mosque in the Purana Qila built by Sher Shah Suri
#Text=Sher Mandal , Purana Qila . 09:00 - 17:00 .
#Text=The two storeyed library inside Purana Qila .
#Text=It is in this library that Humayun fell from stairs and died
#Text=Humayun Darwaza , Purana Qila .
#Text=A gate built by Humayun located in Purana Qila .
#Text=It is the southeast gate of the fort .
#Text=Talaqi Darwaza , Purana Qila .
#Text=The northern gate of Purana Qila .
#Text=It has a marble carving of warring lions with a man in front .
#Text=Purana Qila Baoli ( Stepwell ) , Located within the Purna Qila Complex .
#Text=A small elongagted step well ( baoli ) located near the Qila-i-Kuhna Masjid and Sher Mandal
#Text=Hammam ( Bath House ) ( Located within the Purna Qila Complex ) .
#Text=Located next to the Sher Mandal the ruined hammam ( bath house ) have remains of terracotta pipes and ribber water chutes .
